.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH heal 1  "heal " 
.SH NAME
heal \- Heal bookmarks by resolving and updating their status
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBheal\fR [\fB\-\-file\fR] [\fB\-\-lang\fR] [\fB\-\-auto\-archive\fR] [\fB\-\-archive\-after\fR] [\fB\-\-collection\fR] [\fB\-\-validate\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Heal bookmarks by resolving and updating their status
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-file\fR \fI<FILE>\fR
Heal only bookmarks for this file
.TP
\fB\-\-lang\fR \fI<LANG>\fR
Filter by language (swift, rust, typescript, python)
.TP
\fB\-\-auto\-archive\fR
Archive bookmarks stale beyond grace period
.TP
\fB\-\-archive\-after\fR \fI<ARCHIVE_AFTER>\fR [default: 7]
Days before stale bookmarks are archived
.TP
\fB\-\-collection\fR \fI<COLLECTION>\fR
Filter by collection
.TP
\fB\-\-validate\-only\fR
Skip recording resolution history (only update status)
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Bypass commit ancestry check (allow healing backward in history)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
